result.execSummary:
The defendant Samantha J.R. KANNICK was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Controlled Substance (Adderall), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Expungement is ordered under Section 973.015 upon successful completion of the sentence, no further criminal law violations or ordinance violations involving drugs or alcohol.   The Court finds that the defendant will benefit and society will not be harmed by expungment in this matter.

records.addlTxt:
NO CONTEST plea entered to the charge.  Convicted.
The Court imposes a $10.00 fine plus costs, total of $275.05, to be paid by 09-14-15 or 6 days county jail for failure to pay.
Expungement is ordered under Section 973.015 upon successful completion of the sentence, no further criminal law violations or ordinance violations involving drugs or alcohol.   The Court finds that the defendant will benefit and society will not be harmed by expungment in this matter.
